<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-30T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-30T17:00:00-05:00" n="136" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d136">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112A/971a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Willard</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-30T18:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 30, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1072. [From War Trade Board] for <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_CTL1">Chadbourne</persName>, No.
                                41, and repeat consuls:</p>
                            <p>Before recommending changes enemy trading list confer British,
                                French, Italian colleagues. If agreement results report in duplicate
                                simultaneously to State Department and to Captain
                                    <persName>Stickney</persName>, United States Embassy, Paris. If
                                disagreement results, send your opinion and variant opinions of
                                colleagues with reasons. In each case give nationality and residence
                                of person or association recommended for addition or removal from
                                list.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>